ted from you, the  \r\nvisitor, and indicates the primary purposes why we collect each type  \r\nof information from you.\r\n\r\nThis website uses cookies to keep track of your session ID. We may  \r\nuse cookies to deliver content specific to your interests. Cookies  \r\nhelp collect important business and technical statistics. The  \r\ninformation in the cookies lets us trace the paths followed by  \r\nvisitors to this website as they move from one page to another. Web  \r\nserver logs allow a count of how many people visit this website and  \r\nevaluate this website\'s visitor capacity. We do not use these  \r\ntechnologies to capture your individual email address or any  \r\npersonally identifying information. This information assists us to  \r\ndesign and arrange web pages in the most user-friendly manner and to  \r\ncontinually improve this website to better meet the needs of all  \r\nvisitors.\r\n\r\n\r\nh2. Personal Information You Choose to Provide\r\n\r\nIf you choose to correspond with us through email, the website owner  \r\nmay retain the content of your email messages together with your  \r\nemail address and responses. E-mail information is requested only so  \r\nwe may communicate directly with you. Personal information that is  \r\ncollected from this website is used to effectively market and provide  \r\nyou with the information you have requested.\r\n\r\nAs a visitor, you will be given the opportunity to notify this  \r\nwebsite\'s owner of your desire not to receive these offers. Such e- \r\nmail will have a properly formatted and effective opt-out service.  \r\nThis service successfully removes you from future mailings, and does  \r\nnot contribute to spam.\r\n\r\n\r\nh2. Security\r\n\r\nA major priority is to provide security for the information attained  \r\nby us from our visitors. We employ industry-recognized security  \r\nsafeguards to protect personally identifiable information. Our  \r\nServers use a combination of firewalls, intrusion detection software  \r\nand password protection designed to protect against unauthorized  \r\nentry and loss, theft, or misuse of personal information. Although we  \r\nwill make every effort to protect personal information, no computer  \r\nsystem is totally immune from hackers and others who might misuse  \r\ninformation. We are not responsible for any breach of security that  \r\nis beyond our reasonable control.\r\n\r\n\r\nh2. Third Party\r\n\r\nThe website owner and website creator, Northwood Mortgage Ltd. are not responsible  \r\nfor the practices employed by websites linked to or from this website  \r\nnor the information or content contained therein. Often, links to  \r\nother websites are provided solely as pointers to information on  \r\ntopics that may be useful to the users of this website.\r\n\r\n\r\nh2. Notification of Changes in this Policy\r\n\r\nThis policy may be revised as new features are added or as law  \r\nrequires. Changes can be made without notification unless it is a  \r\nsubstantial change to our privacy practices that would violate the  \r\nprivacy of our visitors. Please check this site for changes to this  \r\nprivacy policy as our site creators will post any changes 14 days  \r\nbefore effective date.\r\n\r\nIf you have any questions about the terms of this privacy policy,  \r\nplease contact the website owner directly, or the website creator  \r\nusing privacy@northwoodmortgage.com\r\nIf you have reason to believe that your personal information is  \r\nincorrect, or need help with how to opt out, please contact  \r\nsupport@northwoodmortgage.com\r\nThis privacy policy is applicable to all Northwood Mortgage Ltd. created website  \r\nsystems.\r\n\r\n\r\nh2. Disclaimer of Liability\r\n\r\nNeither this website owner, nor any of its officers, employees,  \r\ndirectors, contractors or suppliers make any warranty expressed or  \r\nimplied, including warranties of merchantability or assume any legal  \r\nliability for the accuracy, completen